Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry
produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}; mince a few slices until you have
2 TBSP (4 TBSP for 4 servings). Halve, core, and thinly slice
@long green pepper{1} into strips.

Toss sliced onion and green pepper on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a
drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack for ~{5%minutes} (you'll add more to the sheet then).

While veggies roast, pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}.
Season all over with @fajita spice blend{1%tbsp}, salt, and pepper. Drizzle
with oil and rub to evenly coat.

> Chicken cutlets work best for quick, even cooking.

Once veggies have roasted 5 minutes, remove baking sheet from oven. Carefully add
chicken to empty side.

Return to top rack until chicken is browned and cooked through and veggies are
tender and slightly crisp, ~{15-18%minutes}.

> If veggies are done before chicken, remove from sheet and continue roasting
> chicken.

Transfer chicken to a #cutting board{}; let rest at least ~{5%minutes}.

---

Meanwhile, dice @Roma tomato{1}. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%oz}. Zest and quarter
@lime{1}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine tomato, cilantro, minced onion, and a squeeze of
lime juice. Season with salt and pepper.

In a separate small bowl, combine @sour cream{2%tbsp} with lime zest and a
squeeze of lime juice. Add @water{} 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a
drizzling consistency. Season with salt.

---

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and
pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Thinly slice chicken crosswise.

Divide tortillas between plates and fill with chicken and veggies. Top with
pico de gallo, @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup}, and lime crema. Serve with
remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Serve chicken, veggies, pico de gallo, Monterey Jack, lime crema, and lime
> wedges in separate bowls or plates for a build-your-own fajita bar!